==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dentil
<hw>Den"til</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>dentillus</ets>, for L. <ets>denticulus</ets>. Cf.
<er>Dentelli</er>, <er>Denticle</er>, <er>Dentile</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A small square block or projection in cornices,
a number of which are ranged in an ornamental band; -- used particularly
in the Ionic, Corinthian, and Composite orders.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dentilabial</ent>⟦br⟧
